'''Abibatou Traoré''' (born 1973) is a [[Senegal]]ese writer<ref>{{cite news|url=http://fr.allafrica.com/stories/200501100277.html|title=Sénégal: nouvelle génération d'écrivains femmes : de si fortes lettres|date=8 January 2005|work=[[Sud Quotidien]]|language=French|accessdate=26 October 2010}}</ref> and a member of the "Eminent Minds" panel created by Secretary General [[Kofi Annan]]. This panel was created to make suggestions for the fundamental reformation of the [[United Nations]] as an institution.

