The '''Chairman of Andhra Pradesh Legislative Council''' presides over the upper house of the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislature]]. The Chairman regulates the debates and proceedings of the House. The office was in existence from 1958 to 1985 and again from 2007 when the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Council]] has been reconstituted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://aplegislature.org/web/legislative-council/chairman|title=Chairman|website=aplegislature.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-16}}</ref>
The current Chairman of the council is [[N. M. D. Farooq|N. M. D Farooq]], who was elected on 16 November 2017.
