{{Use British English|date=November 2015}}
'''Tamil National Retrieval Troops (TNRT)''' is a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] Nationalist group who fought for an independent Tamil homeland and aspired to unite [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Tamil Eelam]] to a [[Greater Tamil Nadu]].<ref name="satp">{{cite web|url=http://www.satp.org/satporgtp/countries/india/terroristoutfits/TNRT.htm |title=Tamil National Retrieval Troops (TNRT) |publisher=Satp.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref> It is designated as a [[Terrorist organisation]] by the [[Government of India]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mha.gov.in/uniquepage.asp?Id_Pk=292 |title=Ministry of Home Affairs |publisher=Mha.gov.in |date=2011-12-07 |accessdate=2012-10-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425132802/http://mha.gov.in/uniquepage.asp?id_pk=292 |archivedate=2013-04-25 |df= }}</ref> 
It remains [[List of terrorist organisations in India|banned in India]] as of 2018.<ref name="MHA_BanList">{{cite web|title=List of Banned Organisations|url=https://mha.gov.in/banned-organisations|website=Ministry of Home Affairs, GoI|publisher=Government of India|accessdate=3 May 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503233101/https://mha.gov.in/banned-organisations |archivedate= 3 May 2018}}</ref>


It was founded by P. Ravichandran in the late-1980s and is active in [[Tamil Nadu]] and the [[Karnataka State]]. TNRT was a small group estimated 30 members. It is accused of smuggling and close links with [[LTTE]] and [[Veerappan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.satp.org/satporgtp/countries/india/terroristoutfits/TNRT.htm|title=Tamil National Retrieval Troops (TNRT)|publisher=ww.satp.org}}</ref> In 1990s its leader Ravichandran was an accused of the murder of [[Eelam People's Revolutionary Liberation Front]] (EPRLF) general secretary and the 1991 [[Assassination of Rajiv Gandhi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trackingterrorism.org/group/tamil-national-retrieval-troops-tnrt)|title=Tamil National Retrieval Troops (TNRT)|publisher=www.trackingterrorism.org}}</ref>

